    An enumeration of possible aperture functions: ViaDrill, BackDrill, ComponentDrill, MechanicalDrill, CastellatedDrill, OtherDrill, ComponentPad, SMDPad, BGAPad, ConnectorPad, HeatsinkPad, ViaPad, TestPad, CastellatedPad, FiducialPad, ThermalReliefPad, WasherPad, AntiPad, OtherPad, Conductor, EtchedComponent, NonConductor, CopperBalancing, Border, OtherCopper, ComponentMain, ComponentOutline, ComponentPin, Profile, NonMaterial, Material, Other, and Unknown

    • Enum Constant Detail

      • ViaDrill

        public static final ApertureFunction.Function ViaDrill
        Identifies via holes, plated holes whose sole function is to connect different layers, where there is no intention to insert component leads or mechanical objects.

      • BackDrill

        public static final ApertureFunction.Function BackDrill
        Identifies holes used to remove plating over a sub-span by drilling that sub-span with a larger diameter.

      • ComponentDrill

        public static final ApertureFunction.Function ComponentDrill
        Identifies holes that are used for the attachment and/or electrical connection of component terminations, including pins and wires, to a printed board.

      • MechanicalDrill

        public static final ApertureFunction.Function MechanicalDrill
        Identifies holes with mechanical function (registration, screw, etc.) It applies to drill holes and rout slots.

      • CastellatedDrill

        public static final ApertureFunction.Function CastellatedDrill
        Identifies plated holes cut through by the board edge; used to join PCBs.

      • OtherDrill

        public static final ApertureFunction.Function OtherDrill
        Identifies holes with a function not otherwise specified by the Gerber Layer Format Specification.

      • ComponentPad

        public static final ApertureFunction.Function ComponentPad
        Identifies pads associated with component holes. Only used for through-hole components.

      • SMDPad

        public static final ApertureFunction.Function SMDPad
        Identifies pads belonging to the footprint of an SMD component, whether the corresponding lead is connected or not. Applies only for the normal electrical pads.

      • BGAPad

        public static final ApertureFunction.Function BGAPad
        Identifies pads belonging to the footprint of a BGA component, whether the corresponding lead is connected or not. Applies only for the normal electrical pads.

      • ConnectorPad

        public static final ApertureFunction.Function ConnectorPad
        Identifies edge connector pads. Only applicable for outer layers.

      • HeatsinkPad

        public static final ApertureFunction.Function HeatsinkPad
        Identifies heatsink or thermal pads.

      • ViaPad

        public static final ApertureFunction.Function ViaPad
        Identifies via pads that provides a ring to attach the plating in the barrel. This is reserved for pads that have no other function than making the connection between layers.

      • TestPad

        public static final ApertureFunction.Function TestPad
        Identifies test pads. Only applicable for outer layers.

      • CastellatedPad

        public static final ApertureFunction.Function CastellatedPad
        Identifies pads on plated holes cut through by the board edge.

      • FiducialPad

        public static final ApertureFunction.Function FiducialPad
        Identifies fiducial pads.

      • ThermalReliefPad

        public static final ApertureFunction.Function ThermalReliefPad
        Identifies thermal relief pads electrically connected to the surrounding copper but in a manner that restricts heat flow.

      • WasherPad

        public static final ApertureFunction.Function WasherPad
        Identifies pads around non-plated holes without electrical function. Typically for mechanical reenforcement.

      • AntiPad

        public static final ApertureFunction.Function AntiPad
        Identifies pads with clearing polarity (LPC) whose purpose is to create clearance in a plane. It makes room for a drill pass without connecting to the plane.

      • OtherPad

        public static final ApertureFunction.Function OtherPad
        Identifies pads with a function not otherwise specified in the Gerber Layer Format Specification

      • Conductor

        public static final ApertureFunction.Function Conductor
        Identifies copper whose function is to electrically connect pads or to provide shielding, typically tracks and copper pours such as power and ground planes.

      • EtchedComponent

        public static final ApertureFunction.Function EtchedComponent
        Identifies etched components such a embedded inductors, transformers and capacitors.

      • NonConductor

        public static final ApertureFunction.Function NonConductor
        Identifies copper that does not serve as a conductor, i.e., has no electrical function. Typically text in the PCB such as a part number and version.

      • CopperBalancing

        public static final ApertureFunction.Function CopperBalancing
        Identifies copper added to balance copper coverage for the plating process.
